com.xilinx.rapidwright.rwroute

Interface Routable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    RoutableNode

    public interface Routable
    A Routable Object corresponds to a vertex of the routing resource graph. Each Routable instance is associated with a Node instance. It is denoted as "rnode". The routing resource graph is built "lazily", i.e., Routable Objects (rnodes) are created when needed.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static short capacity
      Each Routable Object can be legally used by one net only

      • getUsersConnectionCounts

        Map<NetWrapper,Integer> getUsersConnectionCounts()
        Gets a map that records users of a Routable instance based on all routed connections. Each user is a NetWrapper instance representing a Net instance. It is often the case that multiple connections of a net are using a same rnode. So we count connections of each user to facilitate the sharing mechanism of RWRoute.
        Returns:
        A map between users, i.e., NetWrapper instances representing by Net instances, and numbers of connections from different users.

      • incrementUser

        void incrementUser(NetWrapper user)
        Adds an user NetWrapper instance to the user map, of which a key is a NetWrapper instance and the value is the number of connections that are using a rnode. If the user is already stored in the map, increment the connection count of the user by 1. Otherwise, put the user into the map and initialize the connection count as 1.
        Parameters:
        user - The user in question.

      • uniqueUserCount

        int uniqueUserCount()
        Gets the number of unique users.
        Returns:
        The number of unique NetWrapper instances in the user map, i.e, the key set size of the user map.

      • decrementUser

        void decrementUser(NetWrapper user)
        Decrements the connection count of a user that is represented by a NetWrapper instance corresponding to a Net instance. If there is only one connection of the user that is using a Routable instance, remove the user from the map. Otherwise, decrement the connection count by 1.
        Parameters:
        user - The user to be decremented from the user map.
